      "properties": {"Node name for S&R": "Note"},
      "widgets_values": [
        "BASE SINGER RENDERER — LTX + IP-Adapter FaceID\n=========================================\n\nUSE THIS WORKFLOW FOR: generating the BASE singer video that\n                          LatentSync will lip-sync on top of.\nEXPECTED SPEED: ~30-45s per 5s clip at 512x512 on RTX 4090 mobile\n\nPIPELINE ROLE:\n  1. This workflow generates a base video of the singer (head + shoulders,\n     subtle motion, NO mouth sync yet)\n  2. IP-Adapter FaceID locks the singer's identity from your reference image\n     into every frame — face shape, eye color, hair, skin tone\n  3. The base video has NO lip movement (singer's mouth stays neutral)\n  4. LatentSync (workflow 05) will then re-render the mouth region in\n     post-processing to sync with the isolated vocals\n\nWHY IP-ADAPTER FACEID?\n  Without it, LTX would generate a generic face that doesn't look like your\n  singer. The IP-Adapter FaceID conditions the model on the singer's\n  reference image so every output frame preserves their identity.\n  Weight 0.85 = strong identity lock (range 0.5-1.0).\n  FaceImage weight 0.7 = how much the face structure is locked.\n\nWIDGET NOTES (LTXImageToVideo):\n- [0,1] width, height = 512, 512 (head+shoulders framing)\n- [2] length = 97 frames (~4s at 25fps)\n- [3] steps = 25\n- [4] context_schedule = 0.5 (LOW motion — keep face stable for LatentSync)\n- [5] cfg = 3.5\n- [6] sampler steps = 30\n- [10] seed\n\nWIDGET NOTES (IPAdapterApplyFaceID):\n- [0] weight = 0.85 (identity strength; 0.5=loose, 1.0=strict)\n- [1] preset = 'plus_v2' (FaceID v2 — best for video)\n- [2] face_image_weight = 0.7\n- [3] use_noise = true (helps with video consistency)\n\nPROMPT TIPS:\n  • Describe the singer's POSITION and POSE, not their appearance\n    (IP-Adapter handles appearance)\n  • Mention 'subtle head motion' so the base has some life\n  • DO NOT mention 'singing', 'talking', or 'mouth open' — that confuses LTX\n  • Keep framing consistent across scenes — head+shoulders only\n\n16GB VRAM TIPS:\n  • LTX 512x512 + IP-Adapter: ~10GB peak (IP-Adapter adds ~1GB)\n  • 768x768 + IP-Adapter: ~14GB → safe but tight\n  • If OOM: lower IP-Adapter weight to 0.7, or use 512x512 only\n\nNEXT STEP:\n  Output MP4 (base_singer_ltx_NNN.mp4) feeds into:\n    workflows/05_latentsync_apply.json\n  which applies the actual lip-sync."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    }
